<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<p>The target Portworx version is 2.6 and Stork version is 2.4.5</p>
<p><strong>Playbook</strong></p>
<p>1. Clone the repository and get the latest code from the develop branch<=
/p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">git clo=
ne https://bitbucket.capgroup.com/scm/plat/cloud_automation.git
cd cloud_automation
git checkout develop
cd cloud_automation/AWS/compute/ansible/playbook</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>2.&nbsp;If it hasn't been installed, install kubectl&nbsp;<span style=3D=
"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">since this is required for the upgrade script</spa=
n></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">wget ht=
tps://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-release/release/v1.19.0/bin/linux/a=
md64/kubectl
chmod +x ./kubectl
mv ./kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>3.&nbsp;Log into OCP cluster</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">oc logi=
n https://ocp-console.dev-int-phx1.capgroup.com:443 --token=3DE5wMdeO8ouNmo=
yDhIXSySlVJFwHUmV0e1kxt51eqSqI</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>4. Run the playbook from the jumpbox server of the cluster</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">ansible=
-playbook -i /home/cpzinfbb00000085s002/ocp-provisioning/ocp-prod.cfg -e "p=
ortworx_version=3D2.6" -e "stork_version=3D2.4.5" day2_ocp_portworx_stork_u=
pgrade.yml</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Manual Steps</strong></p>
<p>1. Download the Portworx upgrade script.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">wget --=
output-document=3Dupgrade.sh https://install.portworx.com/2.6/upgrade=20

</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>2. If it hasn't been installed, install kubectl since this is required f=
or the upgrade script</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">wget ht=
tps://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-release/release/v1.19.0/bin/linux/a=
md64/kubectl
chmod +x ./kubectl
mv ./kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>3. Log into the OCP cluster you are upgrading Portworx on</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">oc logi=
n https://ocp-console.dev-int-phx1.capgroup.com:443 --token=3DE5wMdeO8ouNmo=
yDhIXSySlVJFwHUmV0e1kxt51eqSqI</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>4. Check the available daemon sets</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">$ oc ge=
t ds  -n kube-system
NAME             DESIRED   CURRENT   READY     UP-TO-DATE   AVAILABLE   NOD=
E SELECTOR   AGE
portworx         4         4         4         4            4           &lt=
;none&gt;          1y
portworx-api     4         4         4         4            4           &lt=
;none&gt;          1y
portworx-infra   3         3         3         3            3           &lt=
;none&gt;          1y</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>5. Update the daemonset for portworx. Remove the csibindmount definition=
.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">$ oc ed=
it ds portworx -n kube-system
$ oc edit ds portworx-infra -n kube-system
$ oc edit ds portworx-api -n kube-system


Remove the following lines

        - mountPath: /var/lib/kubelet
          name: csibindmountpath


      - hostPath:
          path: /var/lib/kubelet
          type: ""
        name: csibindmountpath</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>6. Run the Portworx Upgrade</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bash up=
grade.sh</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>7. Get the Kube Version</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">$ oc ve=
rsion
oc v3.11.98
kubernetes v1.11.0+d4cacc0
features: Basic-Auth GSSAPI Kerberos SPNEGO

Server https://ocp-console.dev-int-phx1.capgroup.com:443
openshift v3.11.232
kubernetes v1.11.0+d4cacc0

</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>8. Install StorkCtl Client</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">STORK_P=
OD=3D$(kubectl get pods -n kube-system -l name=3Dstork -o jsonpath=3D'{.ite=
ms[0].metadata.name}') &amp;&amp;
kubectl cp -n kube-system $STORK_POD:/storkctl/linux/storkctl ./storkctl
sudo mv storkctl /usr/local/bin &amp;&amp;
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/storkctl</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>9. Download Stork upgrade script. Replace the kube version (?kbver=3DKUB=
E_VERSION) from the output of the last step.&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">wget --=
output-document=3Dstork.yaml  https://install.portworx.com/2.6?kbver=3Dv1.1=
1.0+d4cacc0&amp;comp=3Dstork</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>10. Update the image registry for stork&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">oc edit=
 deployment stork-scheduler
# e.g. openstorage/stork:2.4.5 -&gt; cgprdregistry.capgroup.com/google_cont=
ainers/kube-scheduler-amd64=20
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><span style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">11.&nbsp;</span><span style=3D"le=
tter-spacing: 0.0px;">Apply the configuration</span></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">oc dele=
te -f stork.yaml
oc apply -f stork.yaml</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>12.&nbsp;Download Lighthouse upgrade script.&nbsp;</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">wget --=
output-document=3Dlighthouse.yaml  https://install.portworx.com/2.6?comp=3D=
lighthouse</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>13. Apply the configuration</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">oc dele=
te -f lighthouse.yaml
oc apply -f lighthouse.yaml</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
</div>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
</div>
    </div>
</body>
